postbody_contents:
<section id="postingbody">
IHC T340 crawler with 6-way blade. THE BLOCK IS CRACKED. This is listed as fair condition because of the block. It cracked because of one of those things you just can't believe, and never expect to happen. If you are interested, I'll explain. I used this crawler and it is a lot of fun and had a lot of power. The engine is a 135CI gas engine, the same as used in a Farmall 340 row crop and other tractors, so as far as I know, it is not a real hard engine to find. Everything worked on the crawler. It has turf treads, so you can drive it across the yard without tearing things up if you don't turn sharp. A few of the cleats are missing, but you don't notice. There were fewer than 10,000 of these made between 1959 and 1965, so they are hard to find in any condition. The previous owner did a lot of work on this machine. My asking price of $5,500 is probably what you'd have to pay for the blade if you could find one. Here is a fairly easy project for someone who wants something few people have.
</section>

The rear entertainment layout of this Keystone Cougar fifth wheel makes it feel a lot like home. Model 327RESWE offers triple slides, plenty of seating and storage throughout, plus more.
As you enter notice the refrigerator and storage pantries located straight ahead. The kitchen continues with an L-shaped counter in one of the large kitchen/living area slides. There is plenty of counter space for prep work, a three burner range, and overhead storage, plus more.
The slide opposite the door also features an L-shaped sofa with optional hide-a-bed including overhead storage along with the kitchen appliances. The slide to the left inside the door just passed the entry closet features a booth dinette and two swivel recliners with overhead storage.
Along the rear wall there is an entertainment center with 40" LCD TV, overhead and lower cabinet storage both above and below, plus along each side of the TV. You can also choose an optional fireplace for those cool chilly nights to keep things cozy and warm. The booth dinette can also be replace with a free standing dinette and four chairs.
Head up the steps to the side aisle bath and front bedroom. The bath features a neo-angle shower, toilet, sink, and linen cabinet. Plus there are dual entry doors. Enter from the hall or from within the front master bedroom.
The master suite provides a quiet retreat with slide out queen size bed. There is a window seat opposite the bed with storage above and below. There is also a full height front wardrobe with sliding doors, plus a nightstand, and corner wardrobe closet that has been prepped for a washer and dryer, plus so much more!

New Cougar at last year price, call Arie and ash for the closeout special price $7000.00 below MSRP.

Enjoy family time in the spacious rear entertainment area in this Cougar 1/2 Ton series fifth wheel by Keystone RV. Model 283RETWE offers triple slides with dual slides in the living area alone, creating the most space for entertaining family and friends inside.

As you enter you will find yourself in the Cougar 1/2 Ton kitchen which features a refrigerator straight ahead along with a three burner range, and double kitchen sink. To the left of the door is a nice size pantry for storage. You will also find overhead cabinets and lower cupboards and drawers to neatly tuck away all of your dishes and things.

The rear entertainment area features opposing slides to create a large space for gathering. There is a u-shaped dinette with overhead storage on the left with plenty of seating for everyone. The opposite side features a sofa with overhead storage. The entire rear wall surrounds a space that is ready with TV hook-ups for an optional 32" TV. On either side of that space, plus below it, you will find more space to store your things.

The front of this unit provides a quiet retreat as you step up to the side aisle bath and front private bedroom. There is a corner linen cabinet on your right at the top of the steps with the bathroom on the left featuring a neo-angle shower, toilet and sink.

The private front bedroom takes you away from the hustle and bustle of family activity in the main living area creating a space where you can get away to rest peacefully on the queen bed provided. This bedroom includes a slide out wardrobe, one bedside wardrobe, nightstand, and more.

I have a Backyard Bombers Little MJH Smoker that I am looking to sell. I bought it a few months ago from someone who wanted to switch to an electric smoker. I typically build my own and I just bought this one more or less to review and see how it cooked and see if there were any design elements that I liked that I could apply to my own designs. It is a perfect size for home use. I have performed about a dozen cooks on it. It takes about 30-40 minutes from the time I light charcoal until the time I load food into it. Over the coarse of the next hour I monitor the temp every 10-15 minutes and after that it holds itself steady. I once ran it for 6 hours at 250 without touching the intake valve once. If you are willing to learn the art of cooking with a wood fired smoker it really isn't any more difficult than running a propane smoker. Add a BBQ Guru and it is just as easy as an electric, but it tastes much better than both!

I'd probably rank condition 6-7 out of 10. It could use a new set of door seals, but they do work as is. There are a few scratches around it from moving it around. Also you can see a little of the smoke shadow on the cook chamber door from the previous owner cracking the firebox door open to try to cool it down (he didn't know how to use it and didn't have an intake valve on it). Everything else is in pretty good shape. I always lined the bottom of the cook chamber with foil and cooked my food either in a pan or with a drip pan below it so I didn't ruin the bottom surface. If you would like the wood base and caster wheels it is sitting on you can take them or leave them, it's your choice. I am just going to through the wood in my wood stove if you don't take it and reuse the wheels for something else. If you have any questions please ask. I can help walk you through how to fire this up and get it running if you would like. This is a good sized smoker for home use, practicing, or competition use. I am not firm on the price, make me a reasonable off and it will be yours.

Below is information from the manufacturer regarding this model: ($1199 MSRP)
The MJH series also brags 2" thick high temp insulation all the way around the entire cooker. 2" of insulation ensures this smoker will perform in any temperature, wind, rain, tornado, or hurricane. . .

The MJH is a vertical style smoker with the fire box below and the cook chamber above. Our unique BBQ design allows perfectly even heat and smoke distribution. The efficiency of our cooking system gives your BBQ just the right amount of smoke flavor.

Exterior Dimensions
Lt. MJH
-Depth 26" (28.5" with thermometer)
-Width 24.5"
- Height 24"

Internal shelf Dimensions (Lt. MJH 2 shelves, The MJH 5 shelves)
-Depth 20"
-Width 20"
-Shelf height spacing 5.5"

postbody_contents:
Elecric dryer with pedistool. Works great. Just bought a new matching set. About 5 years old. Must pick up. No holds.
Have an extra pedistool for frigidaire if any interest! Also have the matching washer if anyone would like to take for parts or scrap.

Interior Features

There are 7 auto dry cycles and 4 dryness levels. There are also 5 temperature settings. The appliance has room for adjusting the combination of settings to fit the required heat and cycle duration of each load. The user has to choose the dryness level that he prefers. While some users prefer thoroughly dried garments, some may go for the slightly damp dryness level.
There is an Auto Shrink Guard option that helps in preserving the size and condition of garments. The user does not have to worry about suddenly not fitting into some clothes. He still should read the full wash and care instructions on clothes, especially those that are obviously delicate or are expensive.
The FRIGIDAIRE GLEQ2152ES operates with a Tumble Care Drying System that ensures that the clothes are thoroughly dried but with their fabrics well-taken care of.
There is a 90 minute timed dry included in the FRIGIDAIRE GLEQ2152ES .

Exterior Features

The FRIGIDAIRE GLEQ2152ES electric dryer comes with electronic controls. These controls may have a modern touch but are still convenient and easy to use. The secret to this ease of use is that dial controls are still included. Cycle selection is done through turning the knob. Modern touches include the LED display, which makes readings easy to read and accurate. The estimated remaining time is on display.

The door is reversible. It is also easy to reverse the door according to the more convenient position. It takes only a few minutes to do the reversing. A reversible door allows easy maneuvering and also allows easy installation.
The exterior's main color is white. However, a Gallery series model with the same set of specifications is also available in black. Whatever the choice of color may be, the FRIGIDAIRE GLEQ2152ES is a combination of modern and traditional, which brings both style and convenience.
There is a control lock feature that ensures that the door is closed while in use.

Dimension Specifications

Depth (including hose and door): 29 1/2 inches
Width: 27 inches
Height: 36 inches
Weight: 105 pounds
Volume: 5.8 cubic feet

325

My shop is discounting brand new Zone Off-Road and Rough Country leveling and full suspension lift kits. If you've been putting it off due to the cost most shops would charge you, or just needing something to help you get through the mud or off-road a little better, then let my shop help you out! I am a small off-road shop in Salina that is leaving a big impact all over the country and helping my customers save money. Adrenaline Fueled 4x4 strives to save you the most money possible and I guarantee I can not only match, but certainly beat my competitors prices and parts on lifts. The lift kits I sell are all backed with a lifetime warranty on all parts. This Warranty actually covers everything. I have been serving the Salina area for over 6 years and bring the best product and strive to give my customers the care and satisfaction they deserve. I can drop ship direct from my manufacturer the lift or leveling kits free of charge and it will be delivered directly to your business or front door of your home. Thank you for checking out my ad.
Adrenaline Fueled 4x4
Salina Kansas

postbody_contents:
Ridge-line aluminum 6'x12' v-nose wheel house Ice shack purchased new in late November of 2014. This shack is in great shape has only been on the ice a few dozen times, it weighs in at about 1100 pounds which is super light for a wheelhouse and is perfect for hauling on the lakes with an ATV, snowmobile, or side by side. It has duel opening back doors which make it easy to load an ATV in and will fit an ATV with tracks without issue. This is the perfect shack for running and gunning due to the ease of raising and lowering of the house itself. The inside is fully spray-foamed inside as well as underneath you could literally keep it heated with a candle. It has 6 holes with catch covers and I have added four boat seats, pedestals, and bases down the center of shack to comfortably fish up to 4 people. Feel free to call me anytime to discuss or arrange a time to come check it out. 605-9two9-3894

Thanks for looking

Cold Weather is here. Are you ready to Save Time, Labor, Material, and Money? Order your custom Top-Spread today!

Check out Top-Spread on YouTube.

Top-Spread skid mounted bale processor to fit your needs! Quick attach to skid, end loader, or telehandler. This Patent Pending design was created by farmers to provide an affordable, maneuverable, easy option. You are able to operate Top-Spread all from the comfort of your seat from loading your bale to quickly chopping and spreading bedding right over your fences or inside livestock buildings. Creating windrows and bunk feeding are made easy by dropping the deflector. All component parts on Top-Spread are common size and replacement wear parts are easily purchased at any farm store. We have the models to fit your needs; round or square bales, wood shavings, alley width, and skid steer model determine your Top-Spread. You can also customize the color to match the equipment in your shed, or stand out! With Top-Spread, users save time, material, labor, and money.

Learn more on our website at www.top-notchmachine.com. You will find links to videos of Top-Spread bale spreader in action, model and attachment options, resources, and Top-Spread owner comments. Call Steve at Top-Notch Machine today with your questions or if you wish to customize your Top-Spread. Six41 228-1101

You are able to operate Top-Spread all from the comfort of your seat from loading your bale to quickly chopping and spreading bedding right over your fences or inside livestock buildings. Creating windrows and bunk feeding are made easy by dropping the deflector. All component parts on Top-Spread are common size and replacement wear parts are easily purchased at any farm store. We have the models to fit your needs; round or square bales, wood shavings, alley width, and skid steer model determine your Top-Spread. You can also customize the color to match the equipment in your shed, or stand out! With Top-Spread, users save time, material, labor, and money.

Learn more on our website at www.top-notchmachine.com. You will find links to videos of Top-Spread bale spreader in action, model and attachment options, resources, and Top-Spread owner comments. Call Steve at Top-Notch Machine today with your questions or if you wish to customize your Top-Spread. Six41 228-1101

Follow us on Twitter or like us on Facebook for the latest from Top-Notch Machine.

postbody_contents:
MAXIMIZE YOUR SKID LOADER PERFORMANCE

Whether running a snowlade, pusher, or snowblower on a skidsteer, one of the largest obstacles
encountered is lack of traction. Snow & Ice make it difficult to get around and do the job efficiently.

True North Attachments has solved this issue by offering a HD truck snow tire/rim combination to maximize your skidsteers performance.

The gripper tread design puts more rubber on the road unleashing all the power that your skid steer already has. At 34-1/2" tall, the increased height profile compared to standard skid steer tires will also increase your ground speed. The Heavy-duty rims are 19-1/2" and have a full 3/8" plate welded around the entire rim providing unparalled strengh & durability. Standard 8 lug bolt pattern.

Better Traction + Higher Speed = Maximized performance

These Tire/rim combos provide for excellent
perfomance on construction sites as well.

PRICE POSTED IS FOR A SET OF (4) TIRES MOUNTED ON RIMS SHIPPED TO YOU

We have two 100% ortho liquid fertilizers, they are both seed safe and have proven results in MN, ND, SD, IA, and Wis. Both products contain EDTA ZINC, EDTA Copper, and HEDTA Iron.

Fast Start 7-17-7 is used at a 2-3 gallon use rate for Corn, beans, beets, wheat, and potatoes. At the 3 gallon rate you will recieve around 1 quart of EDTA zinc.

Clean Field Extra 3-18-18 can be used as a starter for Corn, beans, beets, wheat and potatoes. Our Clean Field Extra can be used at a 10 gallon rate on corn as a total P and K package, replacing the need for a costly application of dry fertilizer. This product is under U.S Patent.

We also have Evergreen a 6-12-7 ortho blend with Iron, Zinc and copper already blended.

We deliver all products direct to the farm, saving you time and money. Please contact me for labels, pricing and University Data. Please visit our website at www.cleanfieldproducts.com

postbody_contents:
Give the gift of music this Christmas! Better yet, save some money and buy this exceptional guitar from me. I am an aging guitar teacher slowly diminishing my stock of instruments to my students and the youngsters among us. This baby is a leftover from my days as a performer.

The guitar is a single resonator. If you don't know what a resonator is than this guitar is probably not for you. However, if you have a son or daughter who is completely obsessed with the guitar, this might make an excellent Christmas gift. A resonator is a special guitar.

A resonator guitar sort of sounds like a combination between a harmonica and a guitar. Imagine if a guitar and a harmonica were to wed and have children~the instrument would sound like this!

Resonators are traditionally blues guitars. They were actually developed for the orchestral stage in the days before amplifiers. CCR loved resonators as does many a blues musician. These sound SaaaWEEET with a slide. If you don't have a slide, go get a three inch socket from the pawn shop (you think the old blues guys spent $35 on a blown glass slide in the deep South or the hills of Appalachia?!? No way! Use a spoon or a beer bottle if you want that authentic sound!)

And yes, this guitar is Chinese made. Guitarists, ask yourself this question honestly: Out of 1.3 BILLION Chinese people, you don't think at least ONE could figure out how to make a decent guitar?? PaaaLEASE.

This guitar sounds GREAT. She's a SINGLE resonator. Your triple coil resonators are $800 to $1200. This will get you that sound without sending you to the poor house.

Alright roadies, I could talk guitar all night. There are many pictures and no she ain't new. If you want a new guitar go to Guitar Center!!!

There are no known defects. Plays like a dream. Seriously, the action is similar to a Gibson set up. Every action and set up can be adjusted by yourself or someone at the music shop. I used to do it myself with wood shavings of maple...it's not hard.

The asking price includes a new set of strings which I will gladly put on for you once I see the CAZASH!!!

Thank you for your interest.

Respectfully, this is a cash only deal. MAKE - AN - OFFER.

I'm a wheeler dealer people. I love to negotiate. However, I'm so good at it you might end up paying more than the asking price.

Good luck and MERRY CHRISTMAS!!!

EMAIL only I KNOW you guitar people get a little feisty!!!

GOD BLESS YOU AND GOD BLESS AMERICA!!!

The Transportation King tires come with a material and workmanship warranty only and warrantied through 2 re-caps (no balance warranty). If you have every attempted to get tires from a distributor warehouse (i.e., factory direct), there would be a signal saying "we don't sell to the people". That sign is telling you that small-scale owner/operators are going to pay 40 to 60 percent more for Heavy truck tires. Our Manufacturing Company is the only U.S.A. tire business that opens its Factory warehouse door to anyone who need to purchase tire products for the trucking industry and the OTR tire business. We will ensure that our premium insignia tires will function as the cheapest price tire per mile to operate of any tire otherwise we'll be better than the competition. Our Company Warranty is founded on the ATP 50,000 complete replacement tread Warranty, the 100,000 pro-rated Guarantee, the casing through 3 re-caps and the tires all being re-groovable. The entire Warranty is 5 year/ 500,000 miles.

postbody_contents:
I have recently acquired a very rare 1800's 40 star American flag. This flag has been held by a private collector since 2001. It has been examined and authenticated as a true period flag By the Flag Research Center in Winchester Massachusetts in 2002 (the original documentation of this examination does accompany the flag). The flag measures 56" X 119" the overall condition is very good with light to moderate wear for the age. I have decided to list the flag here before contacting one of the major auction houses with these thoughts: 1.) the flag belongs in this area due to the historical significance. 2.) A major Auction house will take up to 30-40% between buyer and seller fees. We are a established rare coin dealer from the Boston area with over 30 years of experience. Photos and references will be provided to serious inquires (phone calls only).
This flag could be the center piece of any historical collection or to be used as a major statement piece to attract traffic into a established business. below is the description of the flag from the web site rareflags.com

Period flags are extremely rare. Most people anticipated the 39th state to be the Dakotas, not two states of North Dakota and South Dakota. Therefore, 39 star flags are relatively easy to locate. The jump to 40 stars required people to rapidly adjust to the two Dakotas, but before many people could produce 40 star flags in response, Montana's introduction just 6 days later made 40 star flags obsolete almost immediately. Therefore, very few 40 star flags exist today because very few were produced.

Thank You for taking the time to read this ad and hopefully it reaches the right person.

Adopt a kitten or 2! They need a pal! Nice, loving kittens need new homes. They have never been outside, and are not farm cats. All of the kittens and mother are all small in stature.

There are 3 available. The white one and fluffy black & white one are males!
The striped one with some white, is a female.

They are 8 weeks old and cute as can be! They are very sweet and would need another kitty companion as they are used to buddies. And the love to cuddle and play.

I do have a young mother cat that I could part with to the right home, (last picture). She's a good inside mother, (she's the mother to these kittens) but does like to go outside. (She's not with the babies shown in last picture).

This is Gary, South Dakota. (3 miles form the Minnesota border). I do occasionally go to Brookings or Watertown.

Email or call 60five-27two-27two2. (I DON'T have a cell phone or caller ID); I DO have Voice Mail!

If no response, leave a message, and I'll get back to you. Thanks!

This is over a half cord. I am selling this as 50% Maple, 48% Ash, 2% pine and miscellaneous. Sold as a HALF CORD after taking into consideration the wheel wells.

Price INCLUDES DELIVERY AND NEAT STACKING TO WATERTOWN OR BROOKINGS.

Wood is neat stacked in my truck. Stack is measured as 18 inches high, 6 feet wide and 8 feet 4 inches long. Notice I said NEAT STACKED and NOT THROWN. If you are buying thrown amounts, you are buying far less wood than you think you are buying! Sorry to be the bearer of bad news. Thrown wood is a bit of a trick and yes every firewood guy knows it. This is neat stacked, meaning there is little air space, meaning YOU ARE GETTING FAR MORE WOOD.

How do you know this is .56 of a cord? Check out this website... http://www.maine.gov/ag/firewood.html
I use it all the time.

I sell a good amount of wood and this business depends on repeat customers. What I mean is my reputation is important to me and I want my customers to be HAPPY. :-)

I'm in the firewood business because I love it and because there is no gym in my area! I split this by hand (not that it matters). I just have fun collecting wood and delivering it to people. Wood heat is the best heat in my opinion. There is nothing quite like reading a book by a crackling fire or watching the big game with a roaring hearth!

This particular stack is really a "one stop shop" as far as firewood is concerned. About two rows of the wood are small cuts, about an inch or two in diameter. This means you will have an easy time starting the wood on fire with a bit of newspaper.

Approximately one half of the wood is split ASH. There is no termite wood. There is no punk wood.

Ash smells FANTASTIC when burned and is considered by many to be the connoisseur's firewood. Actually, I normally don't sell my Ash but here you go! Ash smells a little bit like grandma's biscuits...that's the only way I can describe it.

Maple also has a pleasant and neutral aroma. Maple is excellent for cooking or smoking if you have a Weber or a smoker grill.

Ash and Maple have excellent coaling properties. For Ash in particular, about half of the burn time is during coaling. I use Ash for overnights because of its coaling properties. You can easily achieve a 12 hour burn time using Ash and Maple and proper venting techniques on an enclosed wood stove.

Either wood is excellent for an open fireplace or a contained wood stove. This is not the product you find at the gas station. Firewood bundles in this area are commonly made of willow, cotton wood and boxelder. While not "junk" wood those varieties do burn considerably faster than Ash and Maple. Willow and Cottonwood contain about 70% of the heat value of a similar size piece of Ash.

Please email or text. Eight Eight Zero and then Four Five Zero Three. You can call too.

Price INCLUDES DELIVERY AND NEAT STACKING TO WATERTOWN OR BROOKINGS.

I need to deliver to either location in the morning / afternoon due to the condition of my truck.

Truck not included. She's a 1986 Chevrolet Custom Deluxe with a four barrel carb, three on the tree and a great spirit!

Sioux Falls people...I will go that far but I need to be compensated. Make an offer. I have family in Sioux Falls and so maybe it will work out.

This is good wood. This is true, premium quality hardwood firewood. Happy hunting and thank you for your interest.

I will take any offers...but if it is too low I'll just burn it myself!!!

Best regards,

Bradylee

postbody_contents:
SOLD

Offered for sale is one rack of seasoned, hardwood maple firewood. Stack has been medium to small split and single stacked on a rack which is the best for seasoning. Stack is 4 foot high and 11 feet long. Pieces are approximately 15 to 16 inches wide. Stacked and seasoned on a rack...so no bugs or rotting.

The stack is 97% pure maple hard wood. Wood is excellent for open fire places as it has a pleasant aroma. Wood has nice coaling properties as well.

Price INCLUDES delivery and neat stacking to Brookings or Watertown (or in between). (Yes. I'll even stack it under your deck or what have you.) Flights of stairs increase the price...sorry.

Medium to small split wood is nice because it allows you more control. I actually cut this for personal use but my wife wants some of our yard back.

Maple does not attract bugs or insects as much as other woods. If you are buying 'mixed hardwoods' you really are probably not getting hardwoods. You are probably getting a mix of cottonwood, boxelder and willow which has a terrible scent.

Photos include close up shots for identification purposes. The cross stack on the one end is poplar which is also nice. Rubbermaid trash bin for size reference purposes and is not included.

This was about a 100 year old Maple tree I felled, split and seasoned. Much of this wood comes from the base which makes it even harder wood. (Different parts of the tree burn at different rates). Much of this wood can be considered heart wood or pith...the inner, strongest portion of the tree.

Maple is an excellent, clean burning hardwood with a pleasant aroma. A pure stack of Maple such as this is not generally available in our area. Maple is commonly used for cabinetry and baseboards because it is so hard.

I'll throw in the wood rack for $25. Wood racks keep wood from rotting. The wood rack is made out of hopscotched lumber but it works well and you never see it anyway.

This is my past time. I don't really care to negotiate this price. Again, 4 high, 11 long stack of wood...stacked...delivered...97% maple...seasoned on a wood rack...no bugs...no termites...no punk wood. I don't sell the stuff I don't want. I sell a good product.

I'm a nice person to do business with...I'll top it off and give you some kindling to get you started.

Again, this is my hobby and not my job. I do this because I enjoy it. So, if your style of negotiating is unenjoyable, do not contact me.

Please respond by email.

Cash on delivery before stacking.

Thank you.

Hasn't been washed in at least 3 years so nothing to hide. I will give it a service before it leaves my shop as it is due. The oil splashed on the front was from a line popping off while transferring waste oil. currently has the spare tire on the left rear because of one being cut down have 3 more very good firestones to go with it. tires are 10 16 5. I have owned it for 5 years and havent put 100 hours on it. the only reason I'm selling is because I just purchased a 250 john deere. asking $9,000 best offer will consider the right trade, no bikes, sleds, tractors or watercraft. Rated lifting capacity is 1500. comes with a 72in GP bucket. Will listen reasonable offers. 9 k is what I was offered on trade at gehl in clark when they put the lift pump on.

Business Description

Dinner Theater in Continuous Successful Operation for Two Decades.

Here's your opportunity to acquire a successful, Florida dinner theatre, including the ongoing business, buildings, and contents on 10 acres of land located on a major US highway with a 121,000 daily traffic count passing the theatre each day.

This theatre has prospered from almost two decades of Broadway non-stop performances. The business has been endlessly revised and is outfitted with state of the art digital audio and illumination systems. Profitability continues to grow each year, up 30% from 2014. Seating is provided for 400+ with kitchen, full bar, boutique, a loyal staff, technical specialists and award winning artists. At present, many shows and stage sets are being sold to other theatres after a run including the digital sound and lighting sequences. Bookings and shows are well into 2016.

In addition to an effectual marketing staff, the dinner theater website integrates online bookings, accounting and tickets. Along with Broadway musicals, plays and comedies, the theater features nationally renowned music and comedy shows. The operation enjoys five star rankings for performances and restaurant excellence along with exceptional press reviews.

Included in the purchase are hundreds of thousands of dollars in props, drops, wardrobe, wigs, etc. Financial underwriting is achievable with a credit-approved buyer. The price is $1.95 million including real estate valued at $1.2 million, with a verifiable net profit of 24%. This theater is turnkey available without disruption including a vast and faithful customer base.

Although the owner is prideful in continuing to improve the business and processes he wishes to retire. He and his key staff are willing to remain on until the new owner has established their own momentum and continued profitability.

So, if you have given thought of increasing your business without any down time due to unsympathetic northern winters, this could be an abundant opportunity for you and your organization.

For further information and confidentiality agreement please call me at
show contact info
Jaz Zydenbos, Tropic Shores Realty, LLC
Attached Documents
None provided.

Detailed Information
Inventory:Included in asking price. Real Estate:Included in asking price: Furniture, Fixtures, & Equipment (FF&E):Included in asking priceFacilities: Continuously updated, recent improvements include new a/c, new roof, new signage, digital sound and queues pintegrated with latest LED stage and dining room lighting. New signage, parking lot and facade.
Meticulously maintained. Room for expansion, including outdoor concert theater. Sits upon 10 acres, on major US route. Presently reserved ticket funds for advanced shows convey upon sale.

Competition: One of a kind dinner theater within 50 miles of nearest competition. The only continuous entertainment attraction in the area. No competition in the entertainment arena.

Directly across from the theatre, several hundred acres have been developed into a waterfront park and high level housing development.
Please request an NDA. I will send you via email.

Growth & Expansion: Mail base of 75,000. 900 annual memberships.

Area is growing rapidly. One of the best real estate environments in Florida. Average home cost is only $133,000. No income tax. Low property taxes. Average home property tax is $900 annually. It is estimated this area will grow in population 15% in the next five years.

The rear of the theater is available for outdoor concerts virtually doubling the income opportunity.Financing: Negotiable Support & Training: Sellers will stay on with negotiated salaries for as long as needed. People, procedures and product in place. Some employees have been with the business since the beginning over 18 years ago.

Please call for more information.

Jaz Zydenbos
Tropic Shores Realty

postbody_contents:
Offered for sale is an original printing of a WWI Public House Poster. This is the way the news was delivered before the days of the 24 hour news cycle. This is a real and authentic piece of World War One history. This poster would have been displayed in a public house (bar or restaurant).

The poster disperses information regarding World War One.

Some phrases on the poster as follows:
German Colonial Possessions surrendered to the Allies since August, 1914
West Africa Togoland Kamerun South West Africa East Africa Pacific Samoa Islands New Guinea Bismarck Solomon Islands Nauru Islands Mariane Islands Caroline Islands Marshal Islands China Kiautschou

Bottom right corner reads exactly: Printed in Great Britain by JOHNSON, RIDDLE & CO, LD32, Southwark Bride Road, London, S.E.

This is an antiques road show quality poster.

You can have an authentic piece of history for your home or den. This will look great in your game room, library, study or office. This piece is an excellent conversation starter.

The piece has been folded to fit in a book, probably during transport from Britain.

The piece is printed red and black. While many were no doubt printed, few have survived, as you will discover as you search the internet for a comparable price.

This is the type of investment that will increase in value.

I am selling it because my wife and I are moving over seas. We are selling up and sailing to another continent and the more delicate parts of my collections will not survive. I am a map and document collector.

I believe this value to be a true and fair representation of the market.

With this in mind, I have the wherewithal to know that something is only worth as much as the amount for which it can be sold. Please make an offer.

This would make an excellent Christmas gift to a hard-to-shop for intellectual.

Maybe you need to one-up your spouse due to last year's diamond? This-is-THE-gift.

Viewing available with no obligation to buy after screening...that means you need to tell me what you do for a living and where you work. I mean no disrespect. This is CL after all.

Cash only even if you are the bank president.

Thank you for your interest. Will consider any and all offers.

AMSOIL carries a great line of diesel fuel additives that do a great job of cleaning injectors, raising cetane numbers and prevent/reduce freeze ups.
Check out some testimonials:
" Just a note to all the people that follow Mylo and his dealers. If you use the injector cleaner for the Diesel engines it is the best product I have ever used only thing is after you first use it you might want to change your first fuel filter because it not only cleans your injectors and lines but your fuel tanks to."
" The fuel injector cleaner that AMSOIL sells is the only concentrated injector cleaner that I have ever seen that works best. The normal rate of one bottle is 80 gallons I treated 240 gallons with two bottles and noticed immediate improvement on the motor how it ran and the more power I had. This is the only diesel fuel injector cleaner I recommend to everyone does not matter if it's a two cylinder diesel an eight cylinder diesel a six or at 12 you will not go wrong with this product. My fuel economy increased by a quarter of a mile a gallon coming out to North Dakota and I haul cars and trucks for a living and ask like one big bold anchor just think if it was a tanker or reefer a dry van or a flatbed. Do the initial cleaning like Mylo recommends and then just do maintenance behind it you can even use cetane booster that he sells for the maintenance and then run the injector cleaner through once a month or twice a month depending on the type of fuel used Best investment ever."

Contact us or check out our website for more info or to purchase: www.windyacressyn.shopamsoil.com

ABOUT US - www.motorpartsplus.com

MOTOR PARTS PLUS (MP+) has been in the engine and component remanufacturing business continuously since 1982 and we specialize in Cummins Diesel Engines. We are located at 905 S. Washington Street in Kaufman, Texas, have a long history of satisfied customers and ship all over the United States. We use only the best of equipment and parts, with every engine being blueprinted and machined to the most exacting tolerances. All of our blocks are custom-built without the use of any kind of "assembly-line" approach.

While you may find cheaper prices online, there is no greater value as we stand behind our engines 100%. If quality and reputation are important to you, then email us today, go online to order at www.motorpartsplus.com or call / text Barry Caldwell at show contact info today!

THE DETAILS
All of our blocks are bored, the crankshafts, lifters and cams are reground, the rods are reconditioned and the remanufactured long block comes with:

* New Cummins Oil Pump
* New Pistons
* New Rings
* New Gaskets
* New Valve Seals
* New Rod Bearings
* New Main Bearings
* New Cam Bearings
* Freeze Plugs
* Valve Job

We also have Short Blocks, Injectors, Coated & Non-Coated Pistons, Engine Kits, Turbo Chargers, Cylinder Heads, Crankshafts, Connecting Rods and Head Studs, Oil, Antifreeze, etc. We will give you a very competitive bid of all the parts that you may require.

PRICES
5.9 Long Blocks $3,600 plus a $1,400 core charge
6.7 Long Blocks $4,500 plus a $1,400 core charge
5.9 Installation $5,000 (Fluids & Filters included)
6.7 Installation $6,100 (Fluids & Filters included)
7.3 and 6.0 Powerstroke Available (call for pricing)

If you provide a rebuildable core within 30 days, we will refund your core charge in full within 5 business days. Please contact us for shipping cost; it is usually between $170 - $450, depending on whether it ships to a business or residence, and if a liftgate is required. In order to keep our prices low, shipping is the responsibility of the client.

WARRANTY
All of our engines ship with a copy of the MP+ 6 Month, Unlimited Mileage Warranty as well as our direct technical support phone number for any engine, installation, or troubleshooting issues.

INVENTORY
The attached picture is a 2004.5 to 2007 5.9, but we have most models in stock and can usually ship them the next day after payment clears.

Discounted SEMI-GUIDED HUNT on 20,000 acres of Private Land PRICING Archery, Muzzleloader, Rifle 4th Season Special since there are only 40 licenses left at the parks and wildlife!
Bull elk $1995 and Cow elk only $1295. You must have at least 1 bull hunter per cow hunter
to qualify. November 11-15 Semi-Guided on Private land! Prices below are discounted.
4 Day Archery Elk . . .. . .. . .. . .... . .. . .$ 2500 Reduced Down to only... . .. . .. . .. . .... . .. . .... . ... . .. . .... . .. . .. . ... . ..$ 1495
2 Day Antelope. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .$ 1600 Reduced Down to only . . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . .. . .... . .. . ... . .. . ...$ 895
4 Day Deer. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ...$ 2600 Reduced Down to only. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . .. . .... . .. . .. . ... . ...$ 1695
5 Day Trophy Deer. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ....$ 4500 Reduced Down to only. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . ....$ 2395
4 Day Trophy Deer (EOS). . .....$ 4000 Reduced Down to only. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . .. . .... . .. . ... . .. . .... . .... . .. . ..$ 1995*
4 Day Elk . . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .... . .$ 3500 Reduced Down to only. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . .. . ..... . .. . ...$ 1995
4 Day Elk (EOS).... . .. . .. . .. . .. . ...... . .$ 3000 Reduced Down to only. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . .. . ... . .. . .. . ... . .. . .... . ...$ 1695*
2nd animal hunts as adding a buck deer or a cow elk to an existing bull elk hunt is $1500 reduced
down to only $995 this year.
A unique offering is being provided by the requests made. We have a guided elk hunt for 4 days on 20,000 acres in a 1 guide on 4 hunters. The group of 4 hunters must be together and book together.
This is a great way for a group that has a number of hunters that are at different level of elk and shooting skills and for the guide to use each hunter's strong points to work as a team to fill all 4 bull elk tags. There is only 1 team hunt being offered per season.
SPECIAL 4 Day Elk Team Hunt...... . .$ 4500 Reduced Down to each hunter at only. . .. . .. . ... . ...$ 2395





Hunt ID: CO-ElkMDeerAntelope-All-RAIGC-BOG-ARYG
Welcome to the center of the world, the place where east meets west, the plains meet the mountains, the elk and the deer meet the antelope. From here you can drive to any place in the United States or even fly there. You are not only in the place where you hunt in the highest elk density in the world but you are in the legendary elk capitol of the United States, the famous Craig Colorado. From this town of 10,000 people draw an imaginary 100 mile circle and you will not find anywhere that a circle of this size can encompass so many elk. The NW corner of the state is home to over half of the states 375,000 elk. If you come to Craig to see people you may as well stay home.
If you came here to see elk don't waste another minute come see where the elk are made and the highest elk density in the world wraps around you like the glamor of nature at its finest. Colorado is home to the largest elk population in the world and within this big game hunting mecca, Moffat County boasts to two of the largest migratory elk herds in North America and is also a hunting hot spot for deer, antelope and small game. With over 20,000 acres to hunt on 7 different ranches you will be swimming in prime private land and enjoying the success it provides.
That is important to an elk hunter but there continues to be more as Craig unfolds to welcome you in to the hunt of your life. Craig is a bustling town with an extremely strong pro guns attitude that is as strong as its pro-hunting attitude that is extremely refreshing in today's world. Friendly town it is, don't hesitate to say high when you meet someone on the street, they will certainly say hi back. The area is known for its record class Mule deer and not to be slighted the pronghorn Antelope that thrive here have the very rare genes to be able to put the sportsman that kills one in the Boone and Crockett or Pope and Young record book, not to mention SCI's book also.
To hunt here you will want to be with a local, some one that was born and raised here living among these great animals and hunting them at a young age. Then becoming so proficient received his outfitting license early on and has many years of outfitting and guiding to show and build his skill and animal knowledge.
This is your outfitter, a man that has probably seen more elk drop at a shot then most of us have ever seen anywhere at any time. His properties are vast and lay game full in in units GMU003, GMU301, and GMU441. Notice the unique regulation for GMU004 and GMU441 for archers. In those 2 GMU's have a unique archery clause? To hunt public land you must draw the license with the additional clause that states that if you are hunting Private Land in GMU004 and 441 you can use a over the counter archery license. This hunt is conducted on 20,000 acres of private land, so the over the counter archery license is valid for this hunt. Note many people are confused by this clause because it is unique to only about 5 units in the state.
If you are in question feel free to contact the Colorado Parks and Wildlife at show contact info for confirmation. GMU003 and 301 is an archery over the counter private or public as most of the units are at this time. Colorado has some of the most complex license application in the nation, rules like this make up that complexity.
Early seasons, September finds the elk in the high country for rut in GMU004 and GMU441. They will be dodging arrows and muzzleloader bullets as they hear the cow coal of many new ladies and the bugles of bulls that have never been heard in these parts as the archers and muzzleloader hunters try to mystify or harass the love sick bull to come within range of their primitive weapons.
When mid-August rolls out of the summer heat the archers and their tent blinds on waterholes begin to pop up like mushroom after a heavy rain. The antelope hunting all takes place in the flat to rolling terrain of GMU003 and GMU301. This is a great "Low Impact" hunt, one for the youth for his first big game animal or a senior citizen that has not given up and want to hunt with him boys and shoot antelope, the time and the success together will be cherished for the years that make up the rest of their lives.
With September just a memory the Pronghorn antelope slips in under the cover of darkness during the 1st week in October and they are greeted by the antelope hunters toting rifles and the only tents by the water holes are the ones that the hunters are camped in during this usually mild weather.
The deer and elk stay for the most part in the cooler temperatures in GMU004 and GMU441 for their archer, muzzleloader and first couple of gun seasons before the slowly migrate down to the Craig Valley floor where some will spend the winter and others continue south to the Yampa River Valley and Axel basin to spend the winter.
This outfitter learned this migration pattern at an early age and knew that you had to have mountain private land as well as land in the valley if you wanted to hunt all three animals during all seasons.
This is exactly what you will be hunting, where the animals that you have a license for are at the time of your season. Not be told "they are not here yet, or they are below us like many are told each year by other outfitters. The words to remember," Don't miss the Flow!"
These hunts are all about having a safe and good hunt with a guide and outfitter that have lived here most if not all of their lives hunting and guiding this honey hole of hunting. The hunt includes the hunt, guided to the degree of semi-guided with both of you having the same goal, that is to meet the large Rocky Mountain Elk, the largest of the species face to face on his terms and to see who wins the right to brag or eat crow the next day depending on the outcome of the contacted opportunity.
Lodging and meals are the hunters responsibility and the outfitter will provide you with motel phone numbers in Crag that he recommends for his hunters and where you will all meet for breakfast early the first morning to head out in the darkness together after plans with maps, guides and hunters all in the loop. This is the first day of the rest of your life. You are going out west on a famous Colorado elk hunt that will build memories that data confirms that hunters enjoy enough that they return year after year.
You will be required to meet the outfitter at a prearranged location at a specific time early in the morning to start your hunt. If you are late and every one had gone stay in your car with your cell phone and depending on how the day goes they might be able to get back to you. Do not go in the property without the outfitter or guides knowledge.
Time has taught him about people or hunters. It is not a first time hunt for many and they mainly need access to private land where a "Land Stewart" has protected the land and made certain that the animals you are after are there when you get there.
He does no advertise his hunts as 1 on 1 or 2 on 1 hunting, instead it is 3, 4 or even 5 on 1 hunting. This depends on the season and the number of hunters hunting that hunt. If you do want a 1 on 1 or a 2 on 1 there will be a price increase to provide that service. He provides a closer attentiveness to the newer hunter while allowing the more veteran hunters more leeway. If necessary the guide can work elk to the hunters but his only requirement is to check on the hunters once per day. As a norm he will assist you in elk hunting knowledge to direct you to the best places to be, hunt or sit depending on the time of year and where the elk are traveling. He is required by the landowners to always be with the group when anyone is hunting on the land. There is no DIY hunting allowed. He is very skilled and knowledgeable about hunting and hunters and as ones fill put more effort into the ones that have not filled. . . yet.
Some ask about the success rate for elk for the outfitter for the last few years. The success average across the 6 seasons varies every year due to the weather. Elk are very weather dependent for their migration. A good average is 60-75% harvest with 99.9 have at least 1 opportunity during the 5 day season, Archery, Muzzleloader, 1st rifle, 2nd rifle, 3rd rifle and 4th rifle. Archery being the lowest success due to the range restriction and 4th season the highest due to the compacting of the herds due to migration but weather can always be a factor in elk hunting.
Many reasons for the wide span are buck fever. Many hunters get it on deer. When you have an animal 3 times the size of a deer it is extremely apparent you must, must focus on the shoulder not the antlers when you shoot. We have antlers shot off many times because of this. I spoke with a hunter that didn't fill and he had shot 20 rounds, at 5 different bulls, 1 at 90 yards standing broad side and never hit an elk.
The other reason is many are short range ground blind whitetail hunters. The farthest they have ever shot is 50 yards in eastern whitetail states. Because of this a 300 or even 200 yard shot is out of the question. We have had them refuse to shoot an elk standing at 200 yards because they felt it was too far. If they do shoot they shoot that far standing up instead of with a rest or better yet laying down.
I recommend everyone to shoot a 300 yards target before coming out west. An elk is huge with a chance twice the size of a deer. (15x15 vs 36x36) so in theory shooting an elk at 200 years is like shooting a deer at 100 yards. If you can do well on paper at 300 yards you will be one of the 75% not the 25%. I also recommend shooting laying down on the ground this skill is difficult for many to lay down on the ground when hunting but this or to some degree with a rest is an important skill to build. Finally getting from a walking position to down on the ground in a solid position with shooting sticks low or resting the forearm of the rifle on a solid rest is a times even with elk hunting. You only have so much time to get from walking to pulling the trigger before the bull moves of out of sight. These are free ranging elk not high fence elk. They will do everything possible for them to be difficult to shoot, and for that we have no control but will do our best to give you an opportunity for a shot.
I have personally hunted in this area for 35 years and never gone home without a elk. Even the public land elk move into the already high number on the private land as soon as the first shot is fired. The lead cow has been doing it for 15 years and they keep doing it generation after generations because it get so little pressure in comparison to the public land which is wall to wall blaze orange. The public land hunter does a good job of moving even more elk than we already have into our private property. Our private property is pre-scouted before the hunts and local herds spotted. Those have the public land herd by noon on the 1st day. Moving elk are a easier target than the local herds because they are not as familiar with the private property escape routes, while your guide is. If the elk are moving they are everywhere. Just like deer though if they decide to lay down and hold up they will still be there but must be spotted in their beds unless they get up to feed or migrate.
Would allow us to bring a self-contained RV to stay in on the property is a question we get asked but due to the fire danger during the hunting season which is usually announced by the forest service is extreme camping of any type is not allowed on the property. Welcome to the center of the world, the place where east meets west, the plains meet the mountains, the elk and the deer meet the antelope. From here you can drive to any place in the United States or even fly there. You are not only in the place where you hunt in the highest elk density in the world but you are in the legendary elk capitol of the United States, the famous Craig Colorado. From this town of 10,000 people draw an imaginary 100 mile circle and you will not find anywhere that a circle of this size can encompass so many elk. The NW corner of the state is home to over half of the states 375,000 elk. If you come to Craig to see people you may as well stay home. 
If you came here to see elk don't waste another minute come see where the elk are made and the highest elk density in the world wraps around you like the glamor of nature at its finest. Colorado is home to the largest elk population in the world and within this big game hunting mecca, Moffat County boasts to two of the largest migratory elk herds in North America and is also a hunting hot spot for deer, antelope and small game. With over 20,000 acres to hunt on 7 different ranches you will be swimming in prime private land and enjoying the success it provides. 
That is important to an elk hunter but there continues to be more as Craig unfolds to welcome you in to the hunt of your life. Craig is a bustling town with an extremely strong pro guns attitude that is as strong as its pro-hunting attitude that is extremely refreshing in today's world. Friendly town it is, don't hesitate to say high when you meet someone on the street, they will certainly say hi back. The area is known for its record class Mule deer and not to be slighted the pronghorn Antelope that thrive here have the very rare genes to be able to put the sportsman that kills one in the Boone and Crockett or Pope and Young record book, not to mention SCI's book also.
To hunt here you will want to be with a local, some one that was born and raised here living among these great animals and hunting them at a young age. Then becoming so proficient received his outfitting license early on and has many years of outfitting and guiding to show and build his skill and animal knowledge.
This is your outfitter, a man that has probably seen more elk drop at a shot then most of us have ever seen anywhere at any time. His properties are vast and lay game full in in units GMU003, GMU301, and GMU441. Notice the unique regulation for GMU004 and GMU441 for archers. In those 2 GMU's have a unique archery clause? To hunt public land you must draw the license with the additional clause that states that if you are hunting Private Land in GMU004 and 441 you can use a over the counter archery license. This hunt is conducted on 20,000 acres of private land, so the over the counter archery license is valid for this hunt. Note many people are confused by this clause because it is unique to only about 5 units in the state.
If you are in question feel free to contact the Colorado Parks and Wildlife at
show contact info
for confirmation. GMU003 and 301 is an archery over the counter private or public as most of the units are at this time. Colorado has some of the most complex license application in the nation, rules like this make up that complexity.
Early seasons, September finds the elk in the high country for rut in GMU004 and GMU441. They will be dodging arrows and muzzleloader bullets as they hear the cow coal of many new ladies and the bugles of bulls that have never been heard in these parts as the archers and muzzleloader hunters try to mystify or harass the love sick bull to come within range of their primitive weapons.
When mid-August rolls out of the summer heat the archers and their tent blinds on waterholes begin to pop up like mushroom after a heavy rain. The antelope hunting all takes place in the flat to rolling terrain of GMU003 and GMU301. This is a great "Low Impact" hunt, one for the youth for his first big game animal or a senior citizen that has not given up and want to hunt with him boys and shoot antelope, the time and the success together will be cherished for the years that make up the rest of their lives.
With September just a memory the Pronghorn antelope slips in under the cover of darkness during the 1st week in October and they are greeted by the antelope hunters toting rifles and the only tents by the water holes are the ones that the hunters are camped in during this usually mild weather.
The deer and elk stay for the most part in the cooler temperatures in GMU004 and GMU441 for their archer, muzzleloader and first couple of gun seasons before the slowly migrate down to the Craig Valley floor where some will spend the winter and others continue south to the Yampa River Valley and Axel basin to spend the winter.
This outfitter learned this migration pattern at an early age and knew that you had to have mountain private land as well as land in the valley if you wanted to hunt all three animals during all seasons.
This is exactly what you will be hunting, where the animals that you have a license for are at the time of your season. Not be told "they are not here yet, or they are below us like many are told each year by other outfitters. The words to remember," Don't miss the Flow!"
These hunts are all about having a safe and good hunt with a guide and outfitter that have lived here most if not all of their lives hunting and guiding this honey hole of hunting. The hunt includes the hunt, guided to the degree of semi-guided with both of you having the same goal, that is to meet the large Rocky Mountain Elk, the largest of the species face to face on his terms and to see who wins the right to brag or eat crow the next day depending on the outcome of the contacted opportunity. 
Lodging and meals are the hunters responsibility and the outfitter will provide you with motel phone numbers in Crag that he recommends for his hunters and where you will all meet for breakfast early the first morning to head out in the darkness together after plans with maps, guides and hunters all in the loop. This is the first day of the rest of your life. You are going out west on a famous Colorado elk hunt that will build memories that data confirms that hunters enjoy enough that they return year after year.

This is a great way for a group that has a number of hunters that are at different level of elk and shooting skills and for the guide to use each hunter's strong points to work as a team to fill all 4 bull elk tags. There is only 1 team hunt being offered per season.
SPECIAL 4 Day Elk Team Hunt...... . .$ 4500 Reduced Down to each hunter at only. . .. . .. . ... . ...$ 2395





Hunt ID: CO-ElkMDeerAntelope-All-RAIGC-BOG-ARYG
Welcome to the center of the world, the place where east meets west, the plains meet the mountains, the elk and the deer meet the antelope. From here you can drive to any place in the United States or even fly there. You are not only in the place where you hunt in the highest elk density in the world but you are in the legendary elk capitol of the United States, the famous Craig Colorado. From this town of 10,000 people draw an imaginary 100 mile circle and you will not find anywhere that a circle of this size can encompass so many elk. The NW corner of the state is home to over half of the states 375,000 elk. If you come to Craig to see people you may as well stay home.
If you came here to see elk don't waste another minute come see where the elk are made and the highest elk density in the world wraps around you like the glamor of nature at its finest. Colorado is home to the largest elk population in the world and within this big game hunting mecca, Moffat County boasts to two of the largest migratory elk herds in North America and is also a hunting hot spot for deer, antelope and small game. With over 20,000 acres to hunt on 7 different ranches you will be swimming in prime private land and enjoying the success it provides.
That is important to an elk hunter but there continues to be more as Craig unfolds to welcome you in to the hunt of your life. Craig is a bustling town with an extremely strong pro guns attitude that is as strong as its pro-hunting attitude that is extremely refreshing in today's world. Friendly town it is, don't hesitate to say high when you meet someone on the street, they will certainly say hi back. The area is known for its record class Mule deer and not to be slighted the pronghorn Antelope that thrive here have the very rare genes to be able to put the sportsman that kills one in the Boone and Crockett or Pope and Young record book, not to mention SCI's book also.
To hunt here you will want to be with a local, some one that was born and raised here living among these great animals and hunting them at a young age. Then becoming so proficient received his outfitting license early on and has many years of outfitting and guiding to show and build his skill and animal knowledge.
This is your outfitter, a man that has probably seen more elk drop at a shot then most of us have ever seen anywhere at any time. His properties are vast and lay game full in in units GMU003, GMU301, and GMU441. Notice the unique regulation for GMU004 and GMU441 for archers. In those 2 GMU's have a unique archery clause? To hunt public land you must draw the license with the additional clause that states that if you are hunting Private Land in GMU004 and 441 you can use a over the counter archery license. This hunt is conducted on 20,000 acres of private land, so the over the counter archery license is valid for this hunt. Note many people are confused by this clause because it is unique to only about 5 units in the state.
If you are in question feel free to contact the Colorado Parks and Wildlife at show contact info for confirmation. GMU003 and 301 is an archery over the counter private or public as most of the units are at this time. Colorado has some of the most complex license application in the nation, rules like this make up that complexity.
Early seasons, September finds the elk in the high country for rut in GMU004 and GMU441. They will be dodging arrows and muzzleloader bullets as they hear the cow coal of many new ladies and the bugles of bulls that have never been heard in these parts as the archers and muzzleloader hunters try to mystify or harass the love sick bull to come within range of their primitive weapons.
When mid-August rolls out of the summer heat the archers and their tent blinds on waterholes begin to pop up like mushroom after a heavy rain. The antelope hunting all takes place in the flat to rolling terrain of GMU003 and GMU301. This is a great "Low Impact" hunt, one for the youth for his first big game animal or a senior citizen that has not given up and want to hunt with him boys and shoot antelope, the time and the success together will be cherished for the years that make up the rest of their lives.
With September just a memory the Pronghorn antelope slips in under the cover of darkness during the 1st week in October and they are greeted by the antelope hunters toting rifles and the only tents by the water holes are the ones that the hunters are camped in during this usually mild weather.
The deer and elk stay for the most part in the cooler temperatures in GMU004 and GMU441 for their archer, muzzleloader and first couple of gun seasons before the slowly migrate down to the Craig Valley floor where some will spend the winter and others continue south to the Yampa River Valley and Axel basin to spend the winter.
This outfitter learned this migration pattern at an early age and knew that you had to have mountain private land as well as land in the valley if you wanted to hunt all three animals during all seasons.
This is exactly what you will be hunting, where the animals that you have a license for are at the time of your season. Not be told "they are not here yet, or they are below us like many are told each year by other outfitters. The words to remember," Don't miss the Flow!"
These hunts are all about having a safe and good hunt with a guide and outfitter that have lived here most if not all of their lives hunting and guiding this honey hole of hunting. The hunt includes the hunt, guided to the degree of semi-guided with both of you having the same goal, that is to meet the large Rocky Mountain Elk, the largest of the species face to face on his terms and to see who wins the right to brag or eat crow the next day depending on the outcome of the contacted opportunity.
Lodging and meals are the hunters responsibility and the outfitter will provide you with motel phone numbers in Crag that he recommends for his hunters and where you will all meet for breakfast early the first morning to head out in the darkness together after plans with maps, guides and hunters all in the loop. This is the first day of the rest of your life. You are going out west on a famous Colorado elk hunt that will build memories that data confirms that hunters enjoy enough that they return year after year.
You will be required to meet the outfitter at a prearranged location at a specific time early in the morning to start your hunt. If you are late and every one had gone stay in your car with your cell phone and depending on how the day goes they might be able to get back to you. Do not go in the property without the outfitter or guides knowledge.
Time has taught him about people or hunters. It is not a first time hunt for many and they mainly need access to private land where a "Land Stewart" has protected the land and made certain that the animals you are after are there when you get there.
He does no advertise his hunts as 1 on 1 or 2 on 1 hunting, instead it is 3, 4 or even 5 on 1 hunting. This depends on the season and the number of hunters hunting that hunt. If you do want a 1 on 1 or a 2 on 1 there will be a price increase to provide that service. He provides a closer attentiveness to the newer hunter while allowing the more veteran hunters more leeway. If necessary the guide can work elk to the hunters but his only requirement is to check on the hunters once per day. As a norm he will assist you in elk hunting knowledge to direct you to the best places to be, hunt or sit depending on the time of year and where the elk are traveling. He is required by the landowners to always be with the group when anyone is hunting on the land. There is no DIY hunting allowed. He is very skilled and knowledgeable about hunting and hunters and as ones fill put more effort into the ones that have not filled. . . yet.
Some ask about the success rate for elk for the outfitter for the last few years. The success average across the 6 seasons varies every year due to the weather. Elk are very weather dependent for their migration. A good average is 60-75% harvest with 99.9 have at least 1 opportunity during the 5 day season, Archery, Muzzleloader, 1st rifle, 2nd rifle, 3rd rifle and 4th rifle. Archery being the lowest success due to the range restriction and 4th season the highest due to the compacting of the herds due to migration but weather can always be a factor in elk hunting.
Many reasons for the wide span are buck fever. Many hunters get it on deer. When you have an animal 3 times the size of a deer it is extremely apparent you must, must focus on the shoulder not the antlers when you shoot. We have antlers shot off many times because of this. I spoke with a hunter that didn't fill and he had shot 20 rounds, at 5 different bulls, 1 at 90 yards standing broad side and never hit an elk.
The other reason is many are short range ground blind whitetail hunters. The farthest they have ever shot is 50 yards in eastern whitetail states. Because of this a 300 or even 200 yard shot is out of the question. We have had them refuse to shoot an elk standing at 200 yards because they felt it was too far. If they do shoot they shoot that far standing up instead of with a rest or better yet laying down.
I recommend everyone to shoot a 300 yards target before coming out west. An elk is huge with a chance twice the size of a deer. (15x15 vs 36x36) so in theory shooting an elk at 200 years is like shooting a deer at 100 yards. If you can do well on paper at 300 yards you will be one of the 75% not the 25%. I also recommend shooting laying down on the ground this skill is difficult for many to lay down on the ground when hunting but this or to some degree with a rest is an important skill to build. Finally getting from a walking position to down on the ground in a solid position with shooting sticks low or resting the forearm of the rifle on a solid rest is a times even with elk hunting. You only have so much time to get from walking to pulling the trigger before the bull moves of out of sight. These are free ranging elk not high fence elk. They will do everything possible for them to be difficult to shoot, and for that we have no control but will do our best to give you an opportunity for a shot.
I have personally hunted in this area for 35 years and never gone home without a elk. You can't find a denser population in the world then the private land you will be hunting in an area known as the elk capitol of the world. Even the public land elk move into the already high number on the private land as soon as the first shot is fired. The lead cow has been doing it for 15 years and they keep doing it generation after generations because it get so little pressure in comparison to the public land which is wall to wall blaze orange. The public land hunter does a good job of moving even more elk than we already have into our private property. Our private property is pre-scouted before the hunts and local herds spotted. Those have the public land herd by noon on the 1st day. Moving elk are a easier target than the local herds because they are not as familiar with the private property escape routes, while your guide is. If the elk are moving they are everywhere. Just like deer though if they decide to lay down and hold up they will still be there but must be spotted in their beds unless they get up to feed or migrate.
Would allow us to bring a self-contained RV to stay in on the property is a question we get asked but due to the fire danger during the hunting season which is usually announced by the forest service is extreme camping of any type is not allowed on the property. Better yet though is in the town of Craig is a KOA camp ground dedicated to hunters in the fall. It has a large game pole, for skinning and hanging you elk to cool. They provide anything that relates to hanging deer and elk along with hunting.
.
This outfitter books up early each year so by now some slots are already filled.
Thank-you
Greg
Keep-m the point required in your mind when you put in for a license this year. You can put in for an elk point then get a elk license over the counter when you arrive in Colorado for the 2nd or 3rd seasons.
If you would like to shoot a mule deer there is only about a 50% chance of drawing one for private land with no points and you will be running into deer all day when you are elk hunting. I recommend putting in for a deer point this year so you will have one for next year or if you do want to hunt deer with your elk this year then put in for a deer and you will automatically either draw or get a point. Ask Greg for details on how you can build your points and hunt the best areas every year.
